# AWS IoT OTA for STM32G474 + ESP32-AT

Copy this file to `aws.md` and replace placeholders with your values.

Region: **${AWS_REGION}**  
Thing: **${IOT_THING_NAME}**  
OTA stream: **${OTA_STREAM_ID}**  
S3 bucket: **${OTA_S3_BUCKET}**

## Flash layout


MCUboot | `0x08000000` - 48 KB - `build/Release/bootloader/mcuboot.bin`
 - Slot 0 (app) | `0x0800C000` - 208 KB - `build/Release/air-monitor-ota.signed.bin`
 - Slot 1 (OTA staging) | `0x08040000` - 256 KB - written by OTA agent

The signed image places a 0x200 MCUboot image header at `0x0800C000`; application code/vectors run at `0x0800C200`.

## Build and sign firmware

```bash
cp Components/esp32-at/Inc/configuration.h.example Components/esp32-at/Inc/configuration.h
# edit configuration.h with your WiFi and AWS endpoint

cmake --preset Release
cmake --build build/Release
```

Outputs:

- `build/Release/bootloader/mcuboot.bin` —  bootloader
- `build/Release/air-monitor-ota.signed.bin` — signed for slot 0 (USB flash)
- `build/Release/air-monitor-ota-ota.signed.bin` — signed for slot 1 (AWS OTA upload)

## Flash workflow (st-flash)


```bash
st-flash write build/Release/bootloader/mcuboot.bin 0x08000000
st-flash write build/Release/air-monitor-ota.signed.bin 0x0800C000
st-flash reset
```

## Create OTA stream (one-time)

```bash
aws iot create-stream \
  --region ${AWS_REGION} \
  --stream-id ${OTA_STREAM_ID} \
  --description "STM32 OTA firmware stream" \
  --files '[{"fileId": 0, "s3Location": {"bucket": "${OTA_S3_BUCKET}", "key": "ota-update/air-monitor-ota-1.0.0.signed.bin"}}]' \
  --role-arn arn:aws:iam::${AWS_ACCOUNT_ID}:role/ota-role
```

## Manual OTA release

```bash
VERSION=$(tr -d '[:space:]' < VERSION)

aws s3 cp build/Release/air-monitor-ota-ota.signed.bin \
  s3://${OTA_S3_BUCKET}/ota-update/air-monitor-ota-${VERSION}.signed.bin \
  --region ${AWS_REGION}

aws iot update-stream \
  --region ${AWS_REGION} \
  --stream-id ${OTA_STREAM_ID} \
  --files "[{\"fileId\":0,\"s3Location\":{\"bucket\":\"${OTA_S3_BUCKET}\",\"key\":\"ota-update/air-monitor-ota-${VERSION}.signed.bin\"}}]" \
  --role-arn arn:aws:iam::${AWS_ACCOUNT_ID}:role/ota-role

aws iot create-ota-update \
  --region ${AWS_REGION} \
  --ota-update-id air-monitor-ota-${VERSION} \
  --targets arn:aws:iot:${AWS_REGION}:${AWS_ACCOUNT_ID}:thing/${IOT_THING_NAME} \
  --files "[{\"fileName\":\"air-monitor-ota-${VERSION}.signed.bin\",\"fileLocation\":{\"stream\":{\"streamId\":\"${OTA_STREAM_ID}\",\"fileId\":0}}}]" \
  --role-arn arn:aws:iam::${AWS_ACCOUNT_ID}:role/ota-role \
  --protocols MQTT \
  --target-selection SNAPSHOT
```

## GitHub Actions OTA deploy

### Repository variables

| `AWS_REGION` | e.g. `us-east-2` |
| `AWS_ACCOUNT_ID` | 12-digit account ID |
| `AWS_ROLE_ARN` | IAM role for GitHub OIDC (`github-ota-deploy`) |
| `IOT_THING_NAME` | IoT thing name |
| `OTA_S3_BUCKET` | Firmware bucket |
| `OTA_STREAM_ID` | IoT stream ID |
| `OTA_ROLE_ARN` | IoT OTA service role (`ota-role`) |

### GitHub environment

Create a **production** environment and enable required reviewers (recommended for a public repo).

### AWS OIDC role (`github-ota-deploy`)

Trust policy (replace `ORG` and `REPO`):

```json
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Principal": {
        "Federated": "arn:aws:iam::${AWS_ACCOUNT_ID}:oidc-provider/token.actions.githubusercontent.com"
      },
      "Action": "sts:AssumeRoleWithWebIdentity",
      "Condition": {
        "StringEquals": {
          "token.actions.githubusercontent.com:aud": "sts.amazonaws.com"
        },
        "StringLike": {
          "token.actions.githubusercontent.com:sub": [
            "repo:ORG/REPO:ref:refs/tags/v*",
            "repo:ORG/REPO:environment:production"
          ]
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

Permissions policy (least privilege):

```json
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": ["s3:PutObject"],
      "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::${OTA_S3_BUCKET}/ota-update/*"
    },
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": [
        "iot:UpdateStream",
        "iot:CreateOTAUpdate",
        "iot:GetOTAUpdate"
      ],
      "Resource": "*"
    }
  ]
}
```

### Triggers

-*Tag push `v1.1.0` - build, upload to S3, update stream, create OTA job
-*Manual `workflow_dispatch`

## IoT thing policy

The certificate policy for `${IOT_THING_NAME}` must allow Jobs and Streams MQTT topics:

```json
{
  "Effect": "Allow",
  "Action": "iot:Subscribe",
  "Resource": [
    "arn:aws:iot:${AWS_REGION}:${AWS_ACCOUNT_ID}:topic/$aws/things/${IOT_THING_NAME}/jobs/*",
    "arn:aws:iot:${AWS_REGION}:${AWS_ACCOUNT_ID}:topic/$aws/things/${IOT_THING_NAME}/streams/*",
    "arn:aws:iot:${AWS_REGION}:${AWS_ACCOUNT_ID}:topicfilter/$aws/things/${IOT_THING_NAME}/jobs/*",
    "arn:aws:iot:${AWS_REGION}:${AWS_ACCOUNT_ID}:topicfilter/$aws/things/${IOT_THING_NAME}/streams/*"
  ]
},
{
  "Effect": "Allow",
  "Action": "iot:Publish",
  "Resource": [
    "arn:aws:iot:${AWS_REGION}:${AWS_ACCOUNT_ID}:topic/$aws/things/${IOT_THING_NAME}/jobs/*",
    "arn:aws:iot:${AWS_REGION}:${AWS_ACCOUNT_ID}:topic/$aws/things/${IOT_THING_NAME}/streams/*"
  ]
},
{
  "Effect": "Allow",
  "Action": "iot:Receive",
  "Resource": [
    "arn:aws:iot:${AWS_REGION}:${AWS_ACCOUNT_ID}:topic/$aws/things/${IOT_THING_NAME}/jobs/*",
    "arn:aws:iot:${AWS_REGION}:${AWS_ACCOUNT_ID}:topic/$aws/things/${IOT_THING_NAME}/streams/*"
  ]
}
```

## IAM role for OTA service (`ota-role`)

Attach `arn:aws:iam::aws:policy/service-role/AmazonFreeRTOSOTAUpdate` and S3 read access:

```json
{
  "Effect": "Allow",
  "Action": ["s3:GetObject"],
  "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::${OTA_S3_BUCKET}/*"
}
```

Trust policy must allow `iot.amazonaws.com` to assume the role.
